oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Tollgate House
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of a house from the Tollgate family, on Sumac Road in Pulaski, Tennessee. There is two older women, three young women, a boy, and an animal (dog or cat?) on the porch. They are wearing period clothing and the women have their hair pulled back. Dated 1908.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses; Dwellings; Porches
